article.headline: Dayton 85, Duquesne 63
article.story: DAYTON, Ohio (AP) -- Norman Plummer scored 18 points and Dayton used a 16-4 first-half run to pull away from Duquesne in an 85-63 victory on Saturday night. The Dukes (2-14, 0-5 Atlantic 10) led 10-5 after the game's first 3½ minutes before Dayton (9-10, 1-4) took off. Logan White's two free throws, Jimmy Binnie's 3-pointer and a foul shot by Desmond Adedeji preceded Charles Little's dunk for a 13-10 lead. By the time Brian Roberts hit a 3-pointer at the 8:33 mark, the Flyers were on top 21-14. Dayton led 41-27 at the half and by as many as 25 points in the second half. Monty Scott and Roberts each added 11 points and Adedeji had 10 -- hitting all four of his shots from the field. Bryant McAllister scored 19 points, Keith Gayden 17 and Chauncey Duke 12 for Duquesne.
